dinner conversation with eric holt gimenez of food first and campesino a campesino center for latin american studies jump to navigation stanford university center for latin american studies search this site home events dinner conversation with eric holt gimenez of food first and campesino a campesino dinner conversation with eric holt gimenez of food first and campesino a campesino wednesday march 7 2012 6 00pm 8 00pm perspectives on sustainable development in latin america working group invites students to a dinner conversation with eric holt gimenez executive director of food first institute for food and development policy after an academic upbringing in rural education and biology holt gimenez got his latin american start while volunteering with small scale farmers in mexico to improve education water quality livelihood strategies and soil management practices his experience there led to the growth of the campesino a campesino movement wherein farmers use stories and parables to exchange information and innovations holt gimenez is author of campesino a campesino voices from latin america's farmer to farmer movement for sustainable agriculture holt gimenez has since worked at the bank information center in washington dc as the latin america program manager now he is executive director of the oakland based food first whose goal is to eliminate the injustices that cause hunger he recently published food movements unite strategies to transform our food systems students will have the chance to participate in informal but engaging conversation with eric holt gimenez in a small setting to ask questions about his current work career path and visions for sustainable development in latin america please rsvp to ensure enough food rsvp to adeaconu stanford edu eric holt gimenez executive director of food first institute for food and development policy arbuckle cafe 655 knight way business school dinner served rsvp requested to adeaconu stanford edu last updated february 27 2